The paper deals with the design and analysis of communication systems, which is a topic that falls under the Information Theory (cs.IT) sub-category. The use of deep learning algorithms for detection is a key aspect of the paper, which suggests that it could also be classified under the Neural and Evolutionary Computing (cs.NE) sub-category. The paper also mentions the evaluation of the algorithms using experimental data, which could place it under the Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-category. The fact that the paper deals with communication systems suggests that it could also be classified under the Systems and Control (cs.SY) sub-category. Finally, the use of chemical signals for transfer of information suggests that the paper could also be classified under the Multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category.
